node.text:
Sweet Chili Coconut Crusted Tofu with Mango Salsa by @jackfruitfulkitchen 🥥❤️

What’s in your bowl today? 😋

Sweet Chili Coconut Crusted Tofu 🥥
SERVES 4

• 1 16 oz block extra firm tofu, sliced into slabs, pressed for 10 minutes, and sliced into strips

1st bowl ☝

• 1/4 C coconut flour
• 2 TBSP tapioca flour (or cornstarch)
• pinch of salt

2nd bowl✌

• 1 C coconut milk (I used full fat, canned)
• 1 lime, juiced
• 1 TBSP sriracha
• 1 TBSP coconut aminos (or soy sauce)
• 1 TBSP sweetener of choice (I used swerve)
• 1/2 tsp powdered ginger
• 1/2 tsp garlic powder

3rd bowl 🤟🏼

• 1/2 C unsweetened shredded coconut
• 1/2 C GF bread crumbs

Cabbage Slaw 🌿

• 2 C red cabbage, finely sliced
• 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced
• 1/2 C cilantro, finely chopped
• 1 tsp sweetener of choice
• salt and pepper

Mango Salsa 🥭

• 2 yellow mangos, chopped
• 1/2 red onion, chopped
• 1 jalapeno, chopped
• 1 red bell pepper, chopped
• 1 firm avocado, chopped
• 1/4 C cilantro, chopped
• 1 garlic clove, pressed
• 1/2 C cherry tomatoes, chopped
• 1 lime, juiced
• 1/2 tsp salt and pepper
• 1/2 tsp cumin

To Serve:

• Rice
• Sweet Chili Sauce

1️⃣ Arrange 3 bowls with above ingredients. In the order listed, first roll each piece of tofu in bowl #1, dredge in bowl #2, and place in bowl #3 and shake the bowl around to coat. Place coated tofu pieces on a parchment lined baking sheet. Spray lightly with oil if desired
2️⃣ Bake in a 375 degree oven for 30 minutes until slightly golden and crisp.
3️⃣ Prepare slaw and salsa by combining the above ingredients.
4️⃣ Serve coconut tofu over rice, salsa, and slaw with a drizzle of sweet chili sauce.

node.text:
What's in your bowl? Here’s some salad inspo from @growthegrin 🥬✨

Some tips from Holly for the perfect salad 👇🏼

🥬First you need some kind of crunchy, fresh veg (lettuce, rocket, cabbage, carrot, zucchini noodles, radish)
🥕Then you need something warm and delicious (roasted sweet potato, pumpkin, carrot.. any roasted root veg basically.)
🥗Then a protein - (Tofu, tempeh, beans, chickpeas, hummus…)
🍋Then a delicious dressing - I usually love a creamy tahini dressing, however as I have hummus in this salad I opted for a simple vinaigrette (olive oil, wholegrain mustard, apple cider vinegar and honey)
Added bonus - Avocado because Avo is everything🥑

AND BAM - you have a delicious, nourishing and satisfying salad!

node.text:
What’s your favourite way to cook tofu? Check out this bowl of Sweet & Spicy Gochujang Tofu @thrivingonplants🌶😍

SAVE this recipe, try it out!

Serves: 2
Time: 15 mins

Ingredients
250g firm tofu, sliced 
Cornstarch, to coat (optional, see step 1)
1.5 tbsp gochujang
1 tbsp light soy sauce
2 tsp maple syrup
1 tsp sesame oil
1 tsp chilli oil
Pinch of ground white pepper
2 tbsp hot water 

Garnish
Sesame seeds (Tip: I get organic raw white sesame seeds and dry toast them on a pan until golden. It makes ALL the difference) 
Green onions

Method
1. For extra crispy tofu, coat in a light layer of cornstarch. If you skip this step, you can fry straight away, it won’t be as crispy but it’s still just as delicious. 
2. Heat a splash of oil in a frypan over medium heat until hot. Dust off any excess cornstarch on the tofu slices and place into the pan. Cook on both sides until golden and crispy. 
3. In the meantime, mix together the remaining ingredients to make your sauce. 
4. Once the tofu is golden, turn the heat down to low and pour in your sauce. Toss well until sauce has thickened and coated all of the tofu pieces.
5. Garnish with green onions and sesame seeds and serve with rice and cucumbers for an extra crunch! Enjoy immediately while hot. 🤤

node.text:
How do you like your oats? 😋
​
​Here’s some Cookie Dough Overnight Oats by @vancouverwithlove 🍪

Save this recipe for your next breakfast (or dessert!)

Ingredients - Serves 2
* 1 ½ cups rolled oats
* 2 tbsp chia seeds
* 3 tbsp vegan chocolate chips (or cacao nibs)
* 2 tbsp almond or peanut butter
* 3 tbsp maple syrup
* 1 tsp vanilla extract
* 2 cups almond or oat milk
Optional
* 1 scoop your favourite vegan protein powder
Instructions
* In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together. 
* Add wet ingredients and mix thoroughly until combined. 
* Divide mixture between two bowls/storage containers and cover each. 
* Store in fridge overnight until ready to eat. Enjoy!

node.text:
Who loves potatoes? We sure do 😋 Try out these Crispy Roasted Potatoes by @thevegansara 🥔 These are oil-free potatoes are that are DELICIOUS & CRISPY!

What you need: 2 medium high starch potatoes (I used russet) peeled/cut into 1 inch cubes, kosher salt, 1/4 cup warm veggie broth or warm water (sub oil) 1 tbl runny tahini, 1 tsp Dijon mustard, 1/2 tsp smoked paprika, salt/ pepper

🥔What you do: 
1️⃣ Place potato cubes in a large pasta pot, cover with cold water by about 1-2 in. Bring to a boil & add a generous amount of kosher salt. Give a stir. Lower to a simmer & cook until fork tender, not mushy (approx 8-10 min)
2️⃣While potatoes are cooking, in a small mixing bowl whisk together the rest of the ingredients until combined. Set aside.
3️⃣Drain potatoes, no need to dry them. Transfer to a large mixing bowl. Shake & flip the potatoes vigorously in the bowl. The edges will soon become rough & a bit crumbly (approx 1-2 min)
4️⃣ Add reserved sauce to the potatoes & shake again till coated. Use a wooden spoon or spatula if needed to help coat.
5️⃣ Spread potatoes on a large unlined baking sheet in one layer leaving space between each piece. If needed, bake on two sheets using top & bottom racks
6️⃣Roast potatoes at 425 F until bottoms release easily & are crispy (approx 20-25 min) Flip potatoes & roast till bottoms become crispy again (approx 15-20min)
7️⃣ Let cool 2-3 min, till not as hot. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce. I served mine with a mix of equal parts ketchup & mayo, a pinch of smoked paprika, a quick drizzle of vegan Worcestershire sauce & pickle juice 🤤🤤🤤enjoy!!

Looking for more delicious plant-based recipes? 🌿

Head on over to veganbowls.com to find more recipes and explore our 12 edition ebook bundle! ✨

node.text:
Really comforting Coconut Green Curry by @plantbasedrd—perfect to satisfying those curry cravings! ❤️

The tip for a vibrant green and flavourful sauce is all in the blended herbs. This sauce is nice and creamy and pretty easy to customise. Feel free to change out the veggies of your choice when sautéing. 🌱

Coconut Green Curry
1 15 oz can full fat coconut milk
1/2 or 1 cup water or veggie broth
1 1/2 tbsp light soy sauce
1/2 tsp lime zest
3 cloves garlic
1 inch ginger
2 scallions
1/2 jalapeño (optional)
2 tbsp green curry paste
2 scallions
Handful fresh cilantro
Handful fresh basil (if you can find Thai Basil even better)
2 tsp sugar
2 tsp avocado oil or other neutral oil
1/2 white onion, diced
1 cup asparagus, cut into chunks
1 medium zucchini, chopped into chunks
1 (450g) block extra firm tofu, pressed and cubed 
1 cup spinach
Juice of 1/2 a lime 

In a blender, blend up the coconut milk, water, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, jalapeño, scallions, sugar, curry paste, cilantro, and basil and blend until smooth then set aside. Feel free to add more water if you'd like your curry to be a little thinner. In a large pan, add your oil then saute your onion with a pinch of salt until softened. Add in your asparagus and zucchini and saute until they become a vibrant green and cook through. Pour veggies into a bowl and if desired saute your tofu to brown slightly. Pour in your curry sauce to the pan with tofu and bring to a low simmer. Allow to simmer covered for about 5-8 minutes (adjust liquid if desired). Stir in your cooked veggies and spinach, add a squeeze of lime and allow the spinach to wilt. Serve along side some rice and enjoy.

node.text:
What’s in your bowl? Here’s some weekday meal inso from @terianncarty ❤️ This bowl’s packed with rice, chili, and some basil pesto. It’s a extremely simply yet hearty meal 😋.
.
BASIL PESTO
2 cups basil
Handful fresh mint
1 clove garlic smashed
Big handful spinach & arugula mix
1/2 lemon juiced
Heaping tbsp nooch
1/2 cup walnuts
1/4 cup olive oil

What to do:
